JOHANNESBURG - SABC unions are threatening a blackout of all services from 11am on Friday morning if the restructuring and retrenchment processes are not halted. They also want the board to be dissolved. READ: SABC workers to down tools Some staff members have already received retrenchment letters. Unions say their request of exactly how many workers will be affected has not been met. READ: SABC workers call on Ramaphosa to save their jobs On Wednesday, a group of employees drove in a motorcade to the Union Buildings to hand over a memorandum of demands to President Cyril Ramaphosa. One of the demands is for the public broadcaster to be placed under administration.